Weâ€™ll use the following functions throughout this lesson:

int_to_string(x)
Covert a number into its string equivaluent.

int_to_string(4)
## [1] "four"
gt(a, b)
Returns TRUE if a is greater than b, otherwise returns FALSE.

gt(3, 1)
## [1] TRUE
gt(2, 5)
## [1] FALSE
is_even(x)
Returns TRUE is x is even, otherwise returns FALSE.

is_even(34)
## [1] TRUE
is_even(55)
## [1] FALSE
square(x)
Computes the square of x.

square(4)
## [1] 16
add_talk(x, y)
Adds x and y and produces a message about which numbers are being added.

add_talk(5, 3)
## x is 5
## y is 3
## [1] 8
paste_talk(x, y)
Concatenates the strings x and y and produces a message about which stirngs are being concatenated.

paste_talk("red", "head")
## x is red
## y is head
## [1] "redhead"
